# specs/

This directory is **suggestion, not spec**. Restructure freely.

It's where this project keeps its raw, structured requirements (the kind
AI agents read to give project-specific advice). Default layout:

```
specs/
├── README.md           ← you're here
├── HOW-TO-USE.md       ← detailed walkthrough (`luban specs --help` mirrors this)
└── sage/
    └── <topic>/
        ├── scene.md    ← scenario in your own words
        ├── pain.md     ← why this hurts now
        └── mvp.md      ← boundary + user stories + acceptance
```

You don't have to keep this layout. The structure that matters is the
**content delivered to AI** via `../AGENTS.md`. If you want to use single
files (`01-onboarding.md`), or a different methodology (STAR / 5W /
Job Story instead of SAGE), or no methodology at all — go ahead and refactor.

For the full method walkthrough (or to remind yourself how SAGE works),
read `HOW-TO-USE.md` here, or run:

    luban specs --help
